10603008.about: When set, Sanity Fetcher will not layout its children; instead, the layout set on its parent element will be used. Useful if you want to set flex gap or control container tag type.

10603011.description:
Fetches Sanity data of a given collection, and repeats `children` slot content for each row fetched.

[See tutorial video](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1SLoVY3hkQ4) and [GROQ cheat sheet](https://www.sanity.io/docs/query-cheat-sheet).

10603016.about: The ID of the project to use.

10603018.about: The API version to use (if not set, 'v1' will be used) - see https://www.sanity.io/docs/js-client#specifying-api-version.

10603019.about: The token to use (or leave blank for unauthenticated usage) - you can create tokens in the API section of your project (i.e. https://www.sanity.io/manage/personal/project/PROJECT_ID/api#tokens).

10603020.about: Whether you want to use CDN ('false' if you want to ensure fresh data).

10603024.description:
Get your project ID, dataset, and token [here](https://www.sanity.io/manage).

Add 'https://host.plasmicdev.com' (or your app host origin) as an authorized host in the CORS origins section of your Sanity project.

[See tutorial video](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dLeu7I4RsYg).

16376002.about: Document type to be queried (*[_type == DOC_TYPE] shortcut).

01kcr5sXWaOX.about: Filter Option to filter by. Read more (https://www.sanity.io/docs/groq-operators#3b7211e976f6)

rtRUCbuhC-Y8.about: Value to filter by, should be of filter field type

xA3oVbUNz0j-.about: Do not automatically repeat children for every category.
